 

---

An Azure pull request template is essential for ensuring consistency, clarity, and completeness in the pull request process. It provides a standardized format that guides contributors on the necessary information to include, such as a summary of changes, related issues, testing procedures, and adherence to coding standards. This facilitates efficient code reviews by enabling reviewers to quickly understand the context and impact of the changes, thereby improving collaboration and reducing the likelihood of misunderstandings or omissions. Additionally, a pull request template reinforces best practices and helps maintain high-quality code across the project, ultimately contributing to the stability and reliability of the software.

 
